parts:
You are extracting UBX-NAV-RELPOSNED from u-blox PDF manual pages.

This message has TWO different structures:

**UBX-NAV-RELPOSNED-V0 (40 bytes, M8/older):**
| Offset | Type | Name |
|--------|------|------|
| 0 | U1 | version (0x00) |
| 1 | U1 | reserved1 |
| 2 | U2 | refStationId |
| 4 | U4 | iTOW |
| 8 | I4 | relPosN |
| 12 | I4 | relPosE |
| 16 | I4 | relPosD |
| 20 | I1 | relPosHPN |
| 21 | I1 | relPosHPE |
| 22 | I1 | relPosHPD |
| 23 | U1 | reserved2 |
| 24 | U4 | accN |
| 28 | U4 | accE |
| 32 | U4 | accD |
| 36 | X4 | flags |

**UBX-NAV-RELPOSNED-V1 (64 bytes, F9/newer):**
| Offset | Type | Name |
|--------|------|------|
| 0 | U1 | version (0x01) |
| 1 | U1 | reserved0 |
| 2 | U2 | refStationId |
| 4 | U4 | iTOW |
| 8 | I4 | relPosN |
| 12 | I4 | relPosE |
| 16 | I4 | relPosD |
| 20 | I4 | relPosLength |
| 24 | I4 | relPosHeading |
| 28 | U4 | reserved1 |
| 32 | I1 | relPosHPN |
| 33 | I1 | relPosHPE |
| 34 | I1 | relPosHPD |
| 35 | I1 | relPosHPLength |
| 36 | U4 | accN |
| 40 | U4 | accE |
| 44 | U4 | accD |
| 48 | U4 | accLength |
| 52 | U4 | accHeading |
| 56 | U4 | reserved2 |
| 60 | X4 | flags |

Check payload length: 40 bytes = V0, 64 bytes = V1.

IMPORTANT: Name the message based on which version the PDF documents:
- If payload is 40 bytes: name = "UBX-NAV-RELPOSNED-V0"
- If payload is 64 bytes: name = "UBX-NAV-RELPOSNED-V1"

Return using ubx_message_extraction tool.

{
  "ubx_message_extraction": [
    {
      "name": "UBX-NAV-RELPOSNED-V1",
      "description": "Relative positioning information in NED frame",
      "message_class": "0x01",
      "message_id": "0x3c",
      "payload_length": 64,
      "fields": [
        {
          "offset": 0,
          "type": "U1",
          "name": "version",
          "scale": null,
          "unit": null,
          "description": "Message version (0x01 for this version)"
        },
        {
          "offset": 1,
          "type": "U1",
          "name": "reserved0",
          "scale": null,
          "unit": null,
          "description": "Reserved"
        },
        {
          "offset": 2,
          "type": "U2",
          "name": "refStationId",
          "scale": null,
          "unit": null,
          "description": "Reference station ID. Must be in the range 0..4095."
        },
        {
          "offset": 4,
          "type": "U4",
          "name": "iTOW",
          "scale": null,
          "unit": "ms",
          "description": "GPS time of week of the navigation epoch. See the section iTOW timestamps in Integration manual for details."
        },
        {
          "offset": 8,
          "type": "I4",
          "name": "relPosN",
          "scale": null,
          "unit": "cm",
          "description": "North component of relative position vector"
        },
        {
          "offset": 12,
          "type": "I4",
          "name": "relPosE",
          "scale": null,
          "unit": "cm",
          "description": "East component of relative position vector"
        },
        {
          "offset": 16,
          "type": "I4",
          "name": "relPosD",
          "scale": null,
          "unit": "cm",
          "description": "Down component of relative position vector"
        },
        {
          "offset": 20,
          "type": "I4",
          "name": "relPosLength",
          "scale": null,
          "unit": "cm",
          "description": "Length of the relative position vector"
        },
        {
          "offset": 24,
          "type": "I4",
          "name": "relPosHeading",
          "scale": "1e-5",
          "unit": "deg",
          "description": "Heading of the relative position vector"
        },
        {
          "offset": 28,
          "type": "U1[4]",
          "name": "reserved1",
          "scale": null,
          "unit": null,
          "description": "Reserved"
        },
        {
          "offset": 32,
          "type": "I1",
          "name": "relPosHPN",
          "scale": "0.1",
          "unit": "mm",
          "description": "High-precision North component of relative position vector. Must be in the range -99 to +99. The full North component of the relative position vector, in units of cm, is given by relPosN + (relPosHPN * 1e-2)"
        },
        {
          "offset": 33,
          "type": "I1",
          "name": "relPosHPE",
          "scale": "0.1",
          "unit": "mm",
          "description": "High-precision East component of relative position vector. Must be in the range -99 to +99. The full East component of the relative position vector, in units of cm, is given by relPosE + (relPosHPE * 1e-2)"
        },
        {
          "offset": 34,
          "type": "I1",
          "name": "relPosHPD",
          "scale": "0.1",
          "unit": "mm",
          "description": "High-precision Down component of relative position vector. Must be in the range -99 to +99. The full Down component of the relative position vector, in units of cm, is given by relPosD + (relPosHPD * 1e-2)"
        },
        {
          "offset": 35,
          "type": "I1",
          "name": "relPosHPLength",
          "scale": "0.1",
          "unit": "mm",
          "description": "High-precision component of the length of the relative position vector. Must be in the range -99 to +99. The full length of the relative position vector, in units of cm, is given by relPosLength + (relPosHPLength * 1e-2)"
        },
        {
          "offset": 36,
          "type": "U4",
          "name": "accN",
          "scale": "0.1",
          "unit": "mm",
          "description": "Accuracy of relative position North component"
        },
        {
          "offset": 40,
          "type": "U4",
          "name": "accE",
          "scale": "0.1",
          "unit": "mm",
          "description": "Accuracy of relative position East component"
        },
        {
          "offset": 44,
          "type": "U4",
          "name": "accD",
          "scale": "0.1",
          "unit": "mm",
          "description": "Accuracy of relative position Down component"
        },
        {
          "offset": 48,
          "type": "U4",
          "name": "accLength",
          "scale": "0.1",
          "unit": "mm",
          "description": "Accuracy of length of the relative position vector"
        },
        {
          "offset": 52,
          "type": "U4",
          "name": "accHeading",
          "scale": "1e-5",
          "unit": "deg",
          "description": "Accuracy of heading of the relative position vector"
        },
        {
          "offset": 56,
          "type": "U1[4]",
          "name": "reserved2",
          "scale": null,
          "unit": null,
          "description": "Reserved"
        },
        {
          "offset": 60,
          "type": "X4",
          "name": "flags",
          "scale": null,
          "unit": null,
          "description": "Flags",
          "sub_fields": [
            {
              "bit": 0,
              "type": "U:1",
              "name": "gnssFixOK",
              "scale": null,
              "unit": null,
              "description": "A valid fix (i.e within DOP & accuracy masks)"
            },
            {
              "bit": 1,
              "type": "U:1",
              "name": "diffSoln",
              "scale": null,
              "unit": null,
              "description": "1 if differential corrections were applied"
            },
            {
              "bit": 2,
              "type": "U:1",
              "name": "relPosValid",
              "scale": null,
              "unit": null,
              "description": "1 if relative position components and accuracies are valid and, in moving base mode only, if baseline is valid"
            },
            {
              "bit": "4..3",
              "type": "U:2",
              "name": "carrSoln",
              "scale": null,
              "unit": null,
              "description": "Carrier phase range solution status: 0 = no carrier phase range solution, 1 = carrier phase range solution with floating ambiguities, 2 = carrier phase range solution with fixed ambiguities"
            },
            {
              "bit": 5,
              "type": "U:1",
              "name": "isMoving",
              "scale": null,
              "unit": null,
              "description": "1 if the receiver is operating in moving base mode"
            },
            {
              "bit": 6,
              "type": "U:1",
              "name": "refPosMiss",
              "scale": null,
              "unit": null,
              "description": "1 if extrapolated reference position was used to compute moving base solution this epoch. (Flag set for protocol versions 27.10, and 27.11, and 31.11)"
            },
            {
              "bit": 7,
              "type": "U:1",
              "name": "refObsMiss",
              "scale": null,
              "unit": null,
              "description": "1 if extrapolated reference observations were used to compute moving base solution this epoch. (Flag set for protocol versions 27.10, and 27.11, and 31.11)"
            },
            {
              "bit": 8,
              "type": "U:1",
              "name": "relPosHeadingValid",
              "scale": null,
              "unit": null,
              "description": "1 if relPosHeading is valid"
            },
            {
              "bit": 9,
              "type": "U:1",
              "name": "relPosNormalized",
              "scale": null,
              "unit": null,
              "description": "1 if the components of the relative position vector (including the high-precision parts) are normalized"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
